{
  "id": "EUVD-2025-202685",
  "enisaUuid": "b3544534-53de-3929-809f-2ccc4705478f",
  "description": "A flaw in libsoup\u2019s HTTP header handling allows multiple Host: headers in a request and returns the last occurrence for server-side processing. Common front proxies often honor the first Host: header, so this mismatch can cause vhost confusion where a proxy routes a request to one backend but the backend interprets it as destined for another host. This discrepancy enables request-smuggling style attacks, cache poisoning, or bypassing host-based access controls when an attacker supplies duplicate Host headers.",
  "datePublished": "Dec 11, 2025, 12:30:59 PM",
